courses.learning_outcomes:
1. acquire familiarity with important musical repertoire of Western art music from the period in question;

2. be able to get a more thorough understanding of specific instrumental genres of the 18th to 20th centuries;

3. develop critical and analytical ability when approaching Western art music in general; and eventually

4. enhance skills in interpretation and appreciation of Western art music.

Upon successfully completing this course, students will be able:
a) To formulate and tackle relevant research/artistic questions;
b) To acquire and consolidate research and academic/creative writing skills;
c) To cultivate critical thinking/artistic expressivity.

